      Compares two pairs of comparable objects. The first pair (that is, the first two arguments) is compared. If the result is not 0, it is returned, otherwise the second pair (that is, the third and fourth arguments) is compared, and so on.

      C2 - the type of the second pair of objects
      Parameters:

      o4 - the second object in the second pair
      Returns:
      a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as the earlier pairs are less than, equal to, or greater than the later pairs

    • time

      public static final String time(long ms)
      Converts a number of milliseconds into a short string representation that gives the numbers of days, hours, minutes, seconds, and milliseconds. For example, "2d1h3m45s20ms" represents two days, 1 hour, 3 minutes, fourty-five seconds, and twenty milliseconds.
      Parameters:
      ms - the number of milliseconds
      Returns:
      a string representation of that amount of time
